      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "Office Memorandum UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "text": "TO : Director, FBI DATE November 30, 1954",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "FROM : SAC, Detroit, (65-2677)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "SUBJECT : DETROIT FLYING SAUCER CLUB",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "ESPIONAGE - X",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "Reference is made to a letter from the Director, dated",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "October 8, 1954, to [REDACTED] Detroit 15,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "Michigan, regarding the Detroit flying saucer Club.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "The purpose of this letter is to set out for the information",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "of the Bureau, the activities of Detroit Flying Saucer Club, as",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "they are known. This is done chronologically.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "On May 18, 1954, Mrs. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "[REDACTED] advised that she had been attending meetings concerning",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "flying saucers, rockets to the moon, etc., which she felt could be",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "subversive. On May 27, 1954, [REDACTED] and [REDACTED] Detroit,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "[REDACTED] advised that one GEORGE ADAMSKI, had",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "talked in Detroit on flying saucers. They were alarmed at the nature",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "of the remarks; such as \"We are Americans, but\".....and that we",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "should reduce our arms and would blow ourselves up with the H-Bomb,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "because visitors from outer space were afraid we had started some-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "thing that would get out of hand. Another lecturer in Detroit, was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "[REDACTED] The sponsors of these speakers were [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "[REDACTED] and [REDACTED] According to pamphlets",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "furnished by [REDACTED] a \"Flying Saucer Review Group\" was to be",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "formed. This was headed by [REDACTED] Ferndale,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "Michigan, who uses the pen name, [REDACTED] He is editor",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "[REDACTED] Detroit. They advised that [REDACTED] was",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "[REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "On July 13, 1954, [REDACTED] advised that [REDACTED] was bringing",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "to Detroit, someone who talked to people from Venus, Clarion, etc.,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "who are more highly advanced than earth people. They advocated the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "Golden Rule as the only workable rule. A meeting was to be held on",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "July 15, 1954. [REDACTED] also furnished a letter from one [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "[REDACTED] encouraging him in his interest in flying saucers.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "[REDACTED] felt such an organization could use the flying saucer scare",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "as political propaganda or from a pseudo-religious view. He said",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "they opposed the atomic bomb and warfare.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "[REDACTED] advised she attended the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "July 15, 1954 meeting of the flying saucer group. The purpose was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
